NAME: ChIP-seq analysis tools
Description: ChIP-seq (Chromatin Immunoprecipitation Sequencing) analysis tools are used to analyze data from experiments that combine chromatin immunoprecipitation with next-generation sequencing. These tools help identify DNA binding sites of transcription factors and other proteins, map histone modifications, and analyze chromatin structure. Common tools include MACS (Model-based Analysis of ChIP-Seq) for peak calling and HOMER (Hypergeometric Optimization of Motif EnRichment) for motif discovery.

NAME: ClusPro
Description: ClusPro is a web-based protein-protein docking server that automates the docking process and clusters the resulting models to identify the most likely binding modes. It uses a combination of rigid-body docking, clustering, and energy minimization to predict complex structures, making it accessible for non-expert users.

NAME: Clustal Omega

NAME: COFACTOR (COmplex Formation And TRansformatiOn)

NAME: DOCK
Description: DOCK is one of the oldest and most established molecular docking programs. It generates possible binding orientations (poses) of small molecules (ligands) within a target protein's binding site and scores these poses based on their predicted binding affinities. DOCK is used for virtual screening and lead optimization in drug discovery.

NAME: DynDock
Description: DynDock is a docking program that simulates the dynamic process of ligand binding by incorporating molecular dynamics (MD) simulations into the docking workflow. It aims to provide more realistic predictions of binding modes by considering the flexibility of both the ligand and the target protein.

NAME: EMBL-Bank

NAME: STRING

NAME: STRING
Description: A database that predicts protein-protein interactions and functional associations, providing a comprehensive network of protein interactions.

NAME: STRINGdb

NAME: Swiss-Model

NAME: T-Coffee

NAME: TMHMM

NAME: UCSC Table Browser

NAME: UGENE

NAME: UniProt

NAME: UniProtKB

NAME: Allen Brain Atlas

NAME: LungMAP
Description: A resource that focuses on the molecular and cellular development of the lung, providing data and tools for understanding lung development, function, and diseases.

NAME: National Center for Biotechnology Information (NCBI)
Description: A research institute that hosts and provides access to various bioinformatics resources, databases, and tools for molecular biology research.

NAME: NCBI Sequence Read Archive (SRA)
Description: A database that archives and provides access to high-throughput sequencing data, allowing researchers to retrieve and analyze raw sequencing data sets.

NAME: Plant Expression Database (PLEXdb)
Description: A database that hosts and provides access to gene expression data in plants, supporting research in plant biology and crop improvement.

NAME: Plant Expression Database (PLEXdb)
Description: A database that hosts and provides access to gene expression data in plants, supporting research in plant biology and crop improvement.

NAME: RIKEN Expression Database (RED)
Description: A database that hosts and provides access to transcriptomic data from various tissues and cell types, supporting research in transcriptomics and gene expression analysis.

NAME: RNA-seq Atlas
Description: A resource that hosts and provides access to transcriptomic data from a wide range of tissues and cell types, facilitating the exploration of gene expression profiles and functional analysis.

NAME: Sequence Read Archive (SRA) at EMBL-EBI
Description: A database that archives and provides access to high-throughput sequencing data, similar to the NCBI SRA, hosted by the European Bioinformatics Institute (EMBL-EBI).

NAME: Single Cell Portal
Description: A resource that hosts single-cell transcriptomic data sets, enabling researchers to explore gene expression profiles at the single-cell level.

NAME: T1DBase - Type 1 Diabetes Database
Description: A database that focuses on genetic and genomic information related to type 1 diabetes, providing valuable resources for understanding the genetics and biology of this disease.

NAME: The Cancer Genome Anatomy Project (TCGAP)
Description: A project that aims to characterize the genomic landscape of different cancer types, providing comprehensive data sets for cancer research and precision medicine.

NAME: The RNA Workbench
Description: A collection of tools and resources for analyzing RNA sequence and structure data, facilitating RNA research and analysis.

NAME: UCSC Xena
Description: A platform that integrates and visualizes diverse genomics and transcriptomics data sets, enabling researchers to explore and analyze multi-omics data.

NAME: University of California, Berkeley (UC Berkeley) RNAcentral
Description: A database that provides comprehensive and curated information on non-coding RNA sequences and their annotations, supporting research in RNA biology.

NAME: University of California, Santa Cruz (UCSC) Genome Browser
Description: A web-based tool that allows researchers to explore and analyze genomic data, providing access to annotated genome assemblies and a variety of tracks and tools for data visualization.

NAME: AUGUSTUS
Description: AUGUSTUS is an ab initio gene prediction tool that predicts genes in eukaryotic genomes. It uses a generalized hidden Markov model (GHMM) to identify coding regions, introns, exons, and other gene features. AUGUSTUS is widely used for annotating newly sequenced genomes and improving existing annotations.

NAME: Canadian Open Genetics Repository (COGR)
Description: A database that collects and shares genomic data and associated clinical information for genetic research and diagnosis.

NAME: Canadian Open Genetics Repository (COGR)
Description: A database that collects and shares genomic data and associated clinical information for genetic research and diagnosis.

NAME: Canadian Rare Diseases Models and Mechanisms Network (RDMM)
Description: A research network that focuses on developing and sharing animal models for rare genetic diseases to enhance understanding and treatment development.

NAME: ClinicalTrials.gov
Description: A registry and database of clinical trials, providing information on ongoing and completed trials for various diseases and conditions

NAME: ClinVar
Description: A public database of clinically relevant genetic variants, providing information on variant interpretations and their association with diseases.

NAME: Contrafold
Description: Contrafold is a machine learning-based RNA secondary structure prediction tool. Unlike traditional thermodynamic models, Contrafold uses a probabilistic framework trained on known RNA structures to predict secondary structures with high accuracy.

NAME: Database of Chromosomal Imbalance and Phenotype in Humans Using Ensembl Resources (DECIPHER)
Description: is a database that collects and shares clinical and genomic data of individuals with chromosomal imbalances and associated phenotypes. It provides a platform for researchers and clinicians to analyze and interpret the clinical significance of genomic variations, aiding in the understanding of genotype-phenotype correlations and improving patient care.

NAME: Database of Curated Mutations (DoCM)
Description: A database that curates and provides information on clinically relevant mutations associated with cancer, aiding in precision medicine and targeted therapies.

NAME: Databases of Genomic Variants (DGV)
Description: A collection of databases that provide information on genomic structural variants in the human genome, aiding in the study of genomic variations and their association with diseases.

NAME: Databases of Genomic Variants (DGV)
Description: DGV (Databases of Genomic Variants) is a collection of databases that catalog and provide information on structural variants and copy number variations found in the human genome. It offers valuable resources for studying genomic variations and their potential association with diseases and phenotypic traits.

NAME: DECIPHER
Description: A database that collects and shares genomic and phenotypic data from individuals with rare genetic disorders, aiding in the identification of disease-causing variants.

NAME: DECIPHER
Description: DECIPHER is a database that collects and shares clinical and genomic data of individuals with chromosomal imbalances and associated phenotypes. It aids in the identification of disease-causing genetic variations, allowing researchers and clinicians to analyze and interpret genotype-phenotype correlations and improve the understanding and diagnosis of rare genetic disorders.

NAME: EuroGentest
Description: A network of European laboratories that provides information, education, and quality assessment for genetic testing, promoting high standards in genetic diagnostics.

NAME: EVM (EVidenceModeler)
Description: EVidenceModeler (EVM) is a genome annotation tool that integrates various types of evidence, such as ab initio gene predictions, protein and transcript alignments, to produce comprehensive and accurate gene structure annotations. It combines the strengths of different prediction methods to improve the accuracy of gene models.

NAME: FR3D
Description: FR3D is a software tool for searching and analyzing RNA 3D structures. It allows users to identify and compare structural motifs within RNA 3D structures, facilitating the study of RNA folding, interactions, and evolutionary conservation. FR3D is particularly useful for analyzing large RNA datasets and discovering novel structuralÂ motifs.

NAME: GATK (Genome Analysis Toolkit)
Description: GATK is a comprehensive toolkit for variant discovery in high-throughput sequencing data. Developed by the Broad Institute, GATK includes tools for pre-processing raw sequence data, such as base quality score recalibration and indel realignment, as well as sophisticated algorithms for variant calling, joint genotyping, and variant filtering. GATK is widely used for genomic research and clinical applications due to its robustness and accuracy.

NAME: GeneCards
Description: A database that integrates information on human genes, including genomic location, protein function, expression, and disease associations, aiding in gene-centric research.

NAME: GENEID
Description: GENEID is a software tool for gene prediction in DNA sequences. It uses a heuristic approach to predict the location of genes in genomic sequences by identifying coding regions, introns, and exons. GENEID is particularly useful for annotating new genomes and identifying potential protein-coding regions.

NAME: GeneMark
Description: GeneMark is a family of gene prediction programs that identify protein-coding genes in prokaryotic and eukaryotic genomes. It uses probabilistic models to predict gene structures and has been adapted for various organisms, including bacteria, archaea, and eukaryotes.

NAME: GeneMatcher
Description: GeneMatcher is an online platform that facilitates the matching of individuals with rare genetic conditions to researchers studying similar genes or variants. It promotes collaboration and data sharing among researchers and clinicians, helping to identify potential disease-causing genes and variants and advance genetic research and diagnosis.

NAME: GeneMatcher
Description: A platform that facilitates matching individuals with rare genetic conditions and researchers studying similar genes or variants, promoting collaboration and discovery.

NAME: GeneReviews
Description: A collection of expert-authored, peer-reviewed articles that provide comprehensive information on genetic conditions, including clinical characteristics, management, and genetic testing.

NAME: GeneReviews
Description: A collection of expert-authored, peer-reviewed articles that provide comprehensive information on genetic conditions, including clinical characteristics, management, and genetic testing.

NAME: GeneTests
Description: A resource that offers information on genetic tests, laboratories, and related resources for various genetic conditions, aiding in diagnosis and genetic counseling.

NAME: GeneTests Laboratory Directory
Description: A directory that provides information on genetic testing laboratories worldwide, assisting healthcare providers in finding appropriate testing resources.

NAME: Genetic Alliance Registry and BioBank (GARB)
Description: A registry and biobank for individuals and families affected by genetic conditions, supporting research and fostering patient-centered initiatives.

NAME: Genetic and Rare Diseases Information Center (GARD)
Description: is a resource that provides information and support for individuals, families, and healthcare professionals dealing with genetic and rare diseases. GARD offers access to reliable information on various rare diseases, genetic conditions, and related topics, as well as resources for finding healthcare providers, clinical trials, and support groups. It serves as a central point of access for comprehensive information and assistance related to genetic and rare diseases.

NAME: Genetic and Rare Diseases Information Center (GARD)
Description: A resource that offers information on genetic and rare diseases, providing a central point of access for patients, families, and healthcare professionals.

NAME: Genetic Home Reference
Description: A consumer-friendly resource that provides information on genetic conditions and related genes, offering descriptions, symptoms, and inheritance patterns.

NAME: Genetic Testing Registry (GTR)
Description: A centralized repository of genetic tests and their associated information, helping healthcare providers and researchers access details about available tests and their clinical validity.

NAME: Genetic Testing Registry (GTR)
Description: is a centralized database that provides information on genetic tests and their associated laboratory services. It offers details about the purpose, methodology, and clinical validity of genetic tests, aiding healthcare providers and researchers in accessing reliable and up-to-date information for genetic testing decision-making.

NAME: Genetic Testing Registry (GTR)
Description: A centralized repository of genetic tests and their associated information, helping healthcare providers and researchers access details about available tests and their clinical validity.

NAME: Genetic Testing Registry (GTR)
Description: The Genetic Testing Registry (GTR) is a centralized database that provides information on genetic tests and their associated laboratory services. It offers details about the purpose, methodology, and clinical validity of genetic tests, aiding healthcare providers and researchers in accessing reliable and up-to-date information for genetic testing decision-making.

NAME: Genomic Data Commons (GDC)
Description: A data repository that houses and provides access to large-scale cancer genomic datasets, supporting cancer research and precision medicine.

NAME: Genomic Medicine Alliance (GMA)
Description: An international alliance that promotes and supports the implementation of genomic medicine in healthcare, fostering collaboration and knowledge exchange.

NAME: Genomics England PanelApp
Description: A platform that curates and shares gene panels for clinical genetic testing, providing guidance on gene selection and interpretation.

NAME: GENSCAN
Description: GENSCAN is a gene prediction program that identifies complete gene structures, including exons, introns, and promoter regions, in genomic DNA sequences. It uses probabilistic models to predict gene locations and structures in both single and multiple genes within a sequence.

NAME: Glimmer
Description: Glimmer (Gene Locator and Interpolated Markov ModelER) is a gene prediction tool for prokaryotic genomes. It uses interpolated Markov models (IMMs) to identify coding regions in bacterial, archaeal, and viral genomes, making it highly accurate for small genomes.

NAME: Global Genes
Description: An advocacy organization that supports the rare disease community, providing resources, education, and awareness initiatives

NAME: Global Variome shared LOVD (LSDB)
Description: A platform that enables sharing and integration of genetic variant data across different databases and research groups, fostering collaboration and data harmonization.

NAME: Human Gene Mutation Database (HGMD)
Description: A curated database of disease-causing mutations in human genes, providing information on the molecular basis of inherited diseases.

NAME: Human Gene Mutation Database (HGMD)
Description: is a comprehensive repository of known disease-causing mutations in human genes, providing valuable information for genetic research and clinical diagnostics. It catalogs genetic variants and their associated diseases, aiding in understanding the molecular basis of inherited disorders.

NAME: Human Phenotype Ontology (HPO)
Description: A standardized vocabulary and ontology of phenotypic abnormalities associated with human diseases, facilitating the annotation and analysis of clinical phenotypes.

NAME: JASPAR
Description: JASPAR is an open-access database of curated, non-redundant transcription factor binding profiles. It provides position frequency matrices (PFMs) that represent the DNA binding preferences of transcription factors, which can be used for predicting regulatory regions and understanding gene regulation mechanisms.

NAME: Leiden Open Variation Database (LOVD)
Description: A platform for the collection and sharing of genetic variants and associated phenotypes, supporting genotype-phenotype correlation studies.

NAME: MAKER
Description: MAKER is a genome annotation pipeline designed to produce high-quality gene annotations by integrating various data sources, including ab initio gene predictions, protein and transcript alignments, and repeat masking. MAKER iteratively improves annotations and is suitable for annotating both well-studied and novel genomes.

NAME: MatchMaker Exchange
Description: A network that enables sharing and matching of rare disease genetic and phenotypic data across multiple databases and institutions, facilitating diagnoses and research collaborations.

NAME: MC-Fold and MC-Sym
Description: MC-Fold and MC-Sym are complementary tools for RNA structure prediction. MC-Fold predicts RNA secondary structures using a modular approach, while MC-Sym generates 3D models of RNA structures based on the secondary structures predicted by MC-Fold. Together, they provide a comprehensive framework for RNA structure prediction from sequence to 3D model.

NAME: MedlinePlus Genetics
Description: A resource that provides consumer-friendly information on genetics, genetic conditions, and genetic testing, supporting health education and awareness.

NAME: MFold
Description: MFold is a web-based tool for predicting the secondary structure of single-stranded nucleic acids, such as RNA and DNA. It uses thermodynamic models to predict the most stable secondary structures based on free energy minimization, providing insights into the folding and stability of RNA molecules.

NAME: Mitochondrial Disease Sequence Data Resource (MSeqDR)
Description: A specialized database that focuses on mitochondrial DNA variations associated with mitochondrial diseases, facilitating research and diagnosis.

NAME: Monarch Initiative
Description: An integrated platform that connects genotype and phenotype data to aid in the understanding and diagnosis of rare diseases.

NAME: MutationTaster
Description: MutationTaster is a comprehensive tool for the prediction of the functional effects of sequence alterations, including amino acid substitutions, intronic and synonymous variants, and indels. It integrates information from various databases and prediction tools to assess the potential pathogenicity of mutations. MutationTaster is often used in clinical genetics and research to identify and interpret disease-causingÂ variants.

NAME: MyGene2
Description: An online portal that connects families with rare genetic conditions to researchers studying similar genes or variants, promoting collaboration and discovery.

NAME: National Human Genome Research Institute (NHGRI
Description: : A research institute that focuses on advancing understanding of the human genome and its role in health and disease, supporting genomics research and education.

NAME: National Organization for Rare Disorders (NORD)
Description: An advocacy organization that provides information and resources for rare diseases, supporting patients, families, and researchers.

NAME: OMIM (Online Mendelian Inheritance in Man)
Description: A comprehensive database of human genes and genetic disorders, providing detailed information on gene-disease relationships.

NAME: Online Mendelian Inheritance in Animals (OMIA
Description: is a comprehensive database that provides information on inherited disorders and traits in various animal species. It catalogs genetic mutations, phenotypic descriptions, and associated references, aiding researchers and veterinarians in understanding and managing genetic conditions in animals.

NAME: Online Mendelian Inheritance in Animals (OMIA)
Description: A database of inherited disorders in animals, providing information on genetic conditions and associated genes across various species.

NAME: Online Mendelian Inheritance in Man (OMIM)
Description: A comprehensive database of human genes and genetic disorders, providing detailed information on gene-disease relationships.

NAME: Orphanet
Description: A reference resource on rare diseases and orphan drugs, offering information on epidemiology, clinical features, and genetic aspects of rare diseases.

NAME: Orphanet
Description: A reference resource on rare diseases and orphan drugs, offering information on epidemiology, clinical features, and genetic aspects of rare diseases.

NAME: PASA (Program to Assemble Spliced Alignments)
Description: PASA is a software package that assembles spliced alignments of expressed sequences (ESTs and RNA-Seq) to produce accurate gene structure annotations. It refines existing annotations and can also identify new genes and alternatively spliced isoforms, providing a comprehensive view of the transcriptome.

NAME: PhenomeCentra
Description: A platform for sharing and analyzing phenotypic and genotypic data of rare diseases, facilitating collaboration and discovery.

NAME: PhenomeCentral
Description: A data-sharing platform for rare disease phenotypes, allowing researchers to share and analyze patient phenotype information to improve diagnostics and research

NAME: Phenotypic Overlap through Rare Disease (PhenomeNET)
Description: A computational framework that integrates phenotype data to identify overlapping features and potential disease relationships among rare disorders.

NAME: PolyPhen-2 (Polymorphism Phenotyping v2)
Description: PolyPhen-2 is a tool for predicting the potential impact of amino acid substitutions on the structure and function of proteins. It uses a combination of sequence-based and structure-based features to classify variants as benign, possibly damaging, or probably damaging. PolyPhen-2 is commonly used in the analysis of human genetic variants to assess their potential involvement in disease.

NAME: Rare Disease Foundation
Description: An organization that supports families affected by rare diseases through research, education, and community-building initiatives

NAME: Rare Disease Ontology (RDO)
Description: An ontology that organizes and standardizes terms and concepts related to rare diseases, facilitating data integration and interoperability.

NAME: Rare Disease Registry Framework (RaDaR)
Description: A framework that facilitates the creation and management of rare disease patient registries, enabling data sharing and research collaboration.

NAME: Rare Diseases Models and Mechanisms Network (RDMM)
Description: A research network that focuses on developing and sharing animal models for rare genetic diseases to enhance understanding and treatment development.

NAME: Registry of Rare Diseases Information Specialists (ORDIS)
Description: A registry of rare disease information specialists, providing access to experts who can assist patients, families, and healthcare professionals with rare disease-related inquiries

NAME: Rfam and Infernal
Description: Rfam is a database of RNA families, each represented by multiple sequence alignments and covariance models (CMs). Infernal (INFERence of RNA ALignment) is a software package used to search sequence databases for RNA homologs and to annotate RNA sequences based on Rfam models. Together, they help identify and classify non-coding RNAs in genomic sequences.

NAME: RNAComposer
Description: RNAComposer is an automated tool for RNA 3D structure prediction. It generates three-dimensional models of RNA molecules from their secondary structures using a knowledge-based approach, facilitating the study of RNA folding and interactions.

NAME: RNAfold
Description: RNAfold is part of the ViennaRNA package and is used to predict RNA secondary structures based on minimum free energy (MFE). It calculates the most stable structures and base pair probabilities, helping researchers understand RNA folding dynamics and stability.

NAME: RNAstructure
Description: RNAstructure is a software suite for RNA secondary structure prediction and analysis. It offers tools for predicting folding structures, calculating free energy changes, and identifying conserved structural motifs. It uses dynamic programming algorithms to predict the most stable secondary structures.

NAME: Rosetta for RNA
Description: Rosetta for RNA is a module within the Rosetta suite specifically designed for modeling RNA structures. It uses fragment-based assembly and energy minimization techniques to predict accurate RNA tertiary structures, helping researchers explore RNA folding, docking, and design.

NAME: SAMtools
Description: SAMtools is a suite of programs for interacting with high-throughput sequencing data. It is used for viewing, sorting, merging, and indexing SAM (Sequence Alignment/Map) and BAM (Binary Alignment/Map) files. SAMtools also provides utilities for variant calling, enabling researchers to analyze sequence alignments and perform tasks such as filtering and extracting data from large sequencing datasets.

NAME: SIFT (Sorting Intolerant From Tolerant)
Description: SIFT is a tool used to predict the impact of amino acid substitutions on protein function. It analyzes the degree of conservation of amino acid residues in sequence alignments and predicts whether a substitution will be deleterious or tolerated. SIFT is useful for annotating and prioritizing genetic variants, particularly in the context of disease-related research.

NAME: Simons Searchlight
Description: A research initiative focused on understanding genetic disorders associated with intellectual and developmental disabilities, fostering research collaboration and participant engagement.

NAME: SimRNA
Description: SimRNA is a computational tool for RNA 3D structure prediction and simulation. It uses a coarse-grained model to simulate RNA folding pathways and generate 3D structures, allowing researchers to study RNA dynamics and structural transitions.

NAME: SNAP
Description: SNAP (Semi-HMM-based Nucleic Acid Parser) is an ab initio gene prediction program that identifies genes in genomic DNA sequences. It uses a hidden Markov model (HMM) to predict exons, introns, and complete gene structures. SNAP is often used in combination with other annotation tools to enhance gene predictionÂ accuracy.

NAME: The Genome Aggregation Database (gnomAD)
Description: A resource that aggregates and provides population-scale genetic variation data from exome and genome sequencing, aiding in the interpretation of genetic variants

NAME: Variant Interpretation of Rare Genetic Diseases (VIRGo)
Description: A platform that integrates genomic and phenotypic data to aid in the interpretation of genetic variants associated with rare diseases.

NAME: AutoDock
Description: A molecular docking software used for predicting and analyzing protein-ligand interactions, aiding in virtual screening and drug design

NAME: BEAST (Bayesian Evolutionary Analysis Sampling Trees)
Description: a tool for Bayesian phylogenetic analysis and molecular dating.

NAME: BEDOPS
Description: A collection of tools for manipulating and analyzing genomic intervals in BED format

NAME: BEDTools
Description: a collection of tools for manipulating genomic features, such as intersecting, merging, and comparing genomic intervals

NAME: Bioclipse
Description: an open-source platform for visualizing, analyzing, and modeling biological data, with built-in functionality for cheminformatics and bioinformatics.

NAME: Bioconductor
Description: a collection of R packages for bioinformatics and computational biology analysis.

NAME: BioJava
Description: a Java library for bioinformatics, offering functionality for sequence analysis, structure analysis, and data manipulation.

NAME: Biopython
Description: a Python library for bioinformatics, providing tools and modules for sequence analysis, file parsing, and data manipulation.

NAME: BLAST (Basic Local Alignment Search Tool)
Description: a widely used tool for comparing nucleotide or protein sequences against a database of known sequences

NAME: Bowtie
Description: A short-read aligner for mapping sequencing reads to a reference genome.

NAME: BRAKER2
Description: BRAKER (Gene prediction in BRAchtome and genoME assemblies with RNA-Seq data) is a bioinformatics tool used for gene prediction in genomes by integrating RNA sequencing (RNA-seq) data. It is particularly designed for eukaryotic organisms where gene prediction can be challenging due to complex gene structures and alternative splicing events

NAME: BWA (Burrows-Wheeler Aligner)
Description: A widely-used tool for aligning sequencing reads against a reference genome

NAME: ChimeraX
Description: a molecular visualization and analysis software for exploring 3D structures of macromolecules and molecular complexes.

NAME: Clustal OMEGA
Description: Its more recent version of CLUSTAL. It is a complete redesign of CLUSTAL algorithm that significantly improves alignment speed and results as it uses “divide and conquer” approach, where sequence is split into smaller subsets and aligned independently before merging the alignments. It also incorporates HMM to improve accuracy

NAME: ClustalW
Description: a tool for multiple sequence alignment, used to identify conserved regions in DNA or protein sequences.

NAME: Cufflinks
Description: A suite of tools for transcriptome assembly and differential expression analysis from RNA-Seq data.

NAME: Cytoscape
Description: a powerful software for visualizing and analyzing molecular interaction networks, including protein-protein interactions and signaling pathways

NAME: DESeq2
Description: A widely-used tool for differential gene expression analysis from RNA-Seq data.

NAME: edgeR
Description: A bioinformatics tool for differential gene expression analysis based on RNA-Seq data.

NAME: EMBOSS (European Molecular Biology Open Software Suite)
Description: a collection of command-line tools for molecular biology sequence analysis and manipulation.

NAME: FastQC
Description: a quality control tool for evaluating the quality of high-throughput sequencing data

NAME: Galaxy
Description: a web-based platform for data-intensive biomedical research, providing a wide range of tools and workflows

NAME: GATK (Genome Analysis Toolkit)
Description: a software package for analyzing high-throughput DNA sequencing data, particularly for variant discovery and genotyping

NAME: GeneMark-ES
Description: the GeneMark-ES algorithm that identifies protein coding genes in eukaryotic genomes. This is the only eukaryotic gene finder that can perform gene prediction without curated training sets

NAME: GeneMark.hmm
Description: The GeneMarkS implementation uses an improved version of the gene finding program GeneMark.hmm, heuristic Markov models of coding and non-coding regions and the Gibbs sampling multiple alignment program.

NAME: GeneMarkS
Description: The new gene prediction method, called GeneMarkS, utilizes a non-supervised training procedure and can be used for a newly sequenced prokaryotic genome with no prior knowledge of any protein or rRNA genes.

NAME: GENESCAN
Description: GeneScan is another gene prediction tool that uses a different approach known as the Hidden Markov Model (HMM). It is designed to identify potential protein-coding genes based on characteristic signals and patterns in genomic sequences

NAME: GOLD (Genetic Optimization for Ligand Docking
Description: A widely-used molecular docking software that performs docking simulations to predict protein-ligand binding affinities.

NAME: HHpred
Description: A tool that predicts protein structure and function by combining profile hidden Markov models and homology detection methods. It can identify distant homologs and provide insights into protein structure and functional annotations

NAME: HMMER
Description: a tool for searching sequence databases using profile hidden Markov models (HMMs). It is widely used for protein sequence analysis

NAME: I-TASSER
Description: A widely used tool for protein structure prediction. It combines template-based modeling, ab initio modeling, and structural refinement methods to generate 3D protein models.

NAME: IGV (Integrative Genomics Viewer
Description: a tool for visualizing and exploring genomic data, including alignments, variants, and expression levels

NAME: iTOL
Description: iTOL (Interactive Tree Of Life) is a web-based tool for the visualization, annotation, and customization of phylogenetic trees and other hierarchical data. It allows researchers to explore and interact with tree structures, annotate them with additional information, and customize their appearance

NAME: MEME (Multiple Expectation-Maximization for Motif Elicitation)
Description: a tool for motif discovery in DNA or protein sequences

NAME: Modeller
Description: A tool for comparative protein structure modeling, which generates 3D models by aligning the target protein sequence to known protein structures. It employs satisfaction of spatial restraints and optimization algorithms to refine the models.

NAME: MOE (Molecular Operating Environment)
Description: A comprehensive suite of tools for drug discovery, including molecular docking, virtual screening, and structure-based design.

NAME: Mothur
Description: a bioinformatics tool for analyzing microbial ecology data, particularly for analyzing 16S rRNA gene

NAME: MUSCLE (Multiple Sequence Comparison by Log-Expectation)
Description: a fast tool for multiple sequence alignment, often used for large-scale sequence comparisons

NAME: NCBI Entrez Utilities
Description: a collection of command-line tools for accessing and retrieving data from the NCBI databas

NAME: PEP-FOLD
Description: A tool for de novo protein structure prediction, specifically for small peptides and protein fragments. It uses an original algorithm based on fragment assembly simulations to generate 3D models

NAME: Phyre2
Description: A web-based tool for protein structure prediction that combines homology modeling and ab initio methods. It uses advanced algorithms to generate accurate 3D models based on sequence similarity and structural constraints

NAME: Picard
Description: A set of command-line tools for manipulating and analyzing high-throughput sequencing data in SAM/BAM format

NAME: PyMOL
Description: a molecular visualization system used for visualizing 3D structures of proteins, nucleic acids, and small molecules

NAME: QUARK
Description: A tool for ab initio protein structure prediction that employs fragment assembly and iterative optimization algorithms. It generates 3D models without relying on template structures and can handle large proteins

NAME: RaptorX
Description: A tool for protein structure prediction that integrates template-based modeling, alignment quality assessment, and model refinement algorithms. It utilizes deep learning techniques and advanced algorithms to improve prediction accuracy

NAME: RAST
Description: RAST (Rapid Annotation using Subsystem Technology) is a bioinformatics tool and platform used for the annotation and analysis of microbial genomes. It is designed to provide automated and high-throughput genome annotation, allowing researchers to analyse the functional potential of microbial genomes

NAME: Rossetta
Description: A versatile suite of algorithms for protein structure prediction, refinement, and design. It combines knowledge-based and ab initio methods to generate accurate 3D models and perform protein structure optimization.

NAME: Samtools
Description: A suite of tools for manipulating and analyzing SAM/BAM format files, commonly used in next-generation sequencing data analysis

NAME: Schrödinger Suite
Description: A collection of software tools for structure-based drug design, including molecular docking, virtual screening, and molecular dynamics simulations

NAME: SPAdes
Description: a genome assembly tool for assembling short reads into longer contigs or scaffolds

NAME: STRING
Description: STRING (Search Tool for the Retrieval of Interacting Genes/Proteins) is a bioinformatics resource and database that focuses on protein-protein interactions (PPIs) and functional associations between proteins. It integrates and provides comprehensive information about known and predicted protein interactions from various sources

NAME: SWISS MODEL
Description: A popular tool for homology modeling, which predicts the 3D structure of a protein based on its similarity to experimentally determined protein structures. It utilizes comparative modeling techniques and a large database of protein structures.

NAME: TopHat
Description: a tool for aligning RNA-Seq reads to a reference genome, often used in transcriptome analysis.

NAME: TopHat
Description: A popular RNA-Seq alignment tool that aligns reads to a reference genome and detects splice junctions.

NAME: Velvet
Description: A de novo genome assembly tool optimized for short-read sequencing data.

NAME: ViennaRNA Package
Description: a collection of tools for predicting RNA secondary structures, RNA folding energies, and RNA-RNA interactions
